{
  "texts": [
    "To ensure consistency with the main analysis, interaction terms were included between the predictor of interest and the persona: Baseline (controls only): disclose ~persona + promptBaseline + size: disclose ~log(params) * persona + promptBaseline + identity: disclose ~model * persona + promptThe 'Baseline + identity' specification is identical to the main analysis model (Section 2.7).",
    "The interaction terms are essential because persona effects vary across models.",
    "We use an adjusted R2 metric to penalize for statistical model complexity.",
    "The size model uses 10 parameters while the identity model uses 66, requiring this penalty adjustment to ensure fair comparison of model fit improvements [39].Test 2 (Wald Tests): To confirm that each predictor is statistically significant in its respective model, Type II Wald tests [41] with conversation-level clustered standard errors were conducted.",
    "For the size model, this tested if 'log(params)' and its interaction with persona significantly predict disclosure; for the identity model, this tested if 'model' and its interaction with persona significantly predict disclosure."
  ]
}